article.description: Playing away from campus was  no problem for No. 18 Gonzaga.
article.headline: Turiaf, Morrison score 15 points each
article.linkText: Gonzaga routs in-state rival Eastern Washington
article.story:
SPOKANE, Washington (Ticker) -- Playing away from campus was 
no problem for No. 18 Gonzaga.

Ronny Turiaf and freshman Adam Morrison each scored 15 points as
the Bulldogs continued their domination of in-state opponents
with a 70-49 rout of Eastern Washington at the Spokane Arena.

Gonzaga (9-2) improved to 2-0 at the Spokane Arena, away from
its cozy gym on campus. The sellout crowd was treated to
another display of the team-oriented basketball that improved
the Bulldogs' mark to 3-0 against Washington opponents.

Turiaf's basket capped an 18-4 tear that opened a 25-11
advantage with just under seven minutes left before halftime.
Turiaf and Morrison each had 10 points at the break as the
Bulldogs extended the lead to 41-21.

Eastern Washington (3-9) has lost 18 straight meetings with
Gonzaga. The Eagles blew a 17-point lead in last season's 67-64
defeat and squandered a 16-point lead two seasons ago.
